# End of Support Policy

## Notification Process

When a version approaches end of support:
1. A deprecation notice will be added to the README and release notes
2. An issue will be created tracking the end-of-support timeline
3. A minimum of **30 days notice** will be given before support ends

## Migration Guidance

When upgrading to a new supported version:
- Review the CHANGELOG for breaking changes
- Follow the migration guide (if provided in the release notes)
- Test thoroughly in a non-production environment first

## After End of Support

- The version's code remains available but will not receive updates
- Issues filed against unsupported versions may be closed
- Users are encouraged to upgrade to a supported version